value.value: A portion of endodermis (PO:0000252) that is part of a hypocotyl (PO:0020100).
A portion of parenchyma tissue that is part of a petiole.
A portion of parenchyma tissue that is part of a sepal.
A portion of parenchyma (PO:0005421) tissue that is part of a petal (PO:0009032).
The chloroplast-containing, photosynthetic parenchymatous tissue situated between the two epidermal layers of the leaf or leaf like organs.
The chloroplast-containing, photosynthetic parenchymatous tissue situated between the two epidermal layers of the petal.
The chloroplast-containing, photosynthetic parenchymatous tissue situated between the two epidermal layers of the sepal.
A shoot system meristem (PO:0006079) that is intercalated between two portions of non-meristematic tissue and results in an increase in length as part of primary growth.

definition.value: See subtypes: leaf intercalary meristem (PO:0006346) and stem intercalary meristem (PO:0006347). Not known to occur in roots. Term for primary growth has been requested in GO.

value.value: A portion of phloem (PO:0005417) tissue that develops from the procambium (PO:0025275).

definition.value: In stem or root it is differentiated behind the apical meristem. Primary phloem develops as part of primary growth (GO term for primary growth has been requested).

value.value: A portion of primary phloem (PO:0006075) tissue that has as parts companion cells (PO:0000071, in angiosperms) or albuminous cells (PO:0025412, in gymnosperms) associated with the sieve elements (PO:0025406) and that develops after the protophloem (PO:0006077).

definition.value: Metaphloem develops after a portion of vascular tissue (PO:0009015) has stopped elongating, in the same location as the protophloem, replacing the protophloem. Sieve elements in the metaphloem are larger than in the protophloem. Develops before the secondary phloem, if any is formed.

value.value: A portion of primary phloem (PO:0006075) tissue has as parts the first-formed sieve elements (PO:0025406) at a particular location and does not have companion cells (PO:0000071, in angiosperms) or albuminous cells (PO:0025412, in gymnosperms) associated with the sieve elements.

definition.value: Protophloem is the first primary phloem to develop in any particular location in a portion of vascular tissue (PO:0009015). Sieve elements in the protophloem are smaller than in the metaphloem (PO:0006076). The protophloem usually only lasts a short time before it is replaced by metaphloem.

value.value: A portion of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) that is part of a shoot system (PO:0009006).
A root apical meristem (PO:0020147) that gives rise to a primary root (PO:0020127).
A portion of protoderm (PO:0006210) tissue that is the outermost layer of the shoot apical meristem (PO:0020148), and gives rise to the leaf abaxial epidermis (PO:0006019).
A portion of protoderm (PO:0006210) tissue that is the outermost layer of the shoot apical meristem (PO:0020148), and gives rise to the leaf adaxial epidermis (PO:0006018).
Tissue consisting of tracheids and parenchyma cells, associated with the vascular bundle.

definition.value: Found generally in gymnosperm leaves.

value.value: A portion of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) that gives rise to a root (PO:0009005).
A native plant cell (PO:0025606) is formed by the division of the male archesporial initial. After several mitotic divisions these cells differentiate into pollen mother cells.
A floral structure primordium (PO:0025477) that is committed to the development of an anther (PO:0009066).
A cultured plant callus that is capable of forming plant organs.

definition.value: Plant organs may be formed after the cultured plant callus is treated with plant growth regulators.

value.value: A cultured plant callus (PO:0000009) that is capable of forming somatic embryos.

definition.value: Somatic embryos may be formed after the cultured plant callus is treated with plant growth regulators.

value.value: A maximal portion of parenchyma (PO:0005421) in the center of a shoot axis (PO:0025029) or root (PO:0009005).
A portion of vascular cambium (PO:0005598) that develops from a procambium (PO:0025275) in a vascular bundle (PO:0005020) that is part of a shoot system (PO:0009006).

definition.value: Found in shoot axes (PO:0025029) and vascular leaves (PO:0009025). Portions of fascicular cambium may merge with interfascular cambium (PO:0006201) or the fascicular cambium from adjacent vascular bundles to form a cylinder, or they may remain isolated.

value.value: A portion of vascular cambium (PO:00055980) that develops from cells in an interfascicular region (PO:0006202) that is part of a shoot system (PO:0009006).

definition.value: Portions of interfascicular cambium may merge with fascicular cambium (PO:0006200) to form a cylinder of cambium or they may remain isolated. May develop from meristematic cells (PO:0004010) that have never differentiated into another cell type or from parenchyma cells (PO:0000074) that retain some meristematic ability.

value.value: A portion of ground tissue (PO:0025059) located between vascular bundles in a shoot axis.

definition.value: Inapplicable for nearly all monocots.

value.value: A portion of ground tissue (PO:0025059) that is part of a root stele located between the phloem and endodermis.
A native plant cell (PO:0025606) which is diploid (2n), and undergoes meiosis (GO:0007126) to produce four haploid (1n) plant spores (PO:0025017).
Irregularly-shaped, chlorenchymatous cell, separated by large air spaces.

definition.value: Usually found in the abaxial/lower part of the leaf mesophyll as in a dorsiventral leaf, but between two palisade parenchyma layers in an isobilateral leaf. If you are annotating to this term, please add an additional annotation to vascular leaf (PO:0009025) or non-vascular leaf (PO:0025075), depending on the species. All annotations for angiosperms, gymnosperms, and pteridophytes should go to vascular leaf and all annotations for bryophytes should go to non-vascular leaf.

value.value: Elongated chlorenchymatous cell oriented perpendicular to the leaf surface and which is active in photosynthesis.

definition.value: Usually found in the adaxil/upper part of the leaf mesophyll. If you are annotating to this term, please add an additional annotation to vascular leaf (PO:0009025) or non-vascular leaf (PO:0025075), depending on the species. All annotations for angiosperms, gymnosperms, and pteridophytes should go to vascular leaf and all annotations for bryophytes should go to non-vascular leaf.

value.value: A short cell in the dimorphic type of exodermis with cell wall that remains non-thickened.
Cell in the endodermal layer of the root with cell wall that remains non-thickened.

A portion of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) that is the outer layer of an apical meristem (PO:0020144), or the outer layer of a plant embryo proper (PO:0000001), and gives rise to a portion of epidermis (PO:0005679).

definition.value: A protoderm may or may not arise from independent initial cells (PO:0004011). Some researchers also refer to it as an epidermis in a  meristematic state.

value.value: A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) that is part of an abscission zone (PO:0000146) and contains cells that develop an abnormal wall chemistry and swelling resulting in their easily being pulled apart along the pectin-rich middle lamella (GO:0009519).

definition.value: Directly involved in the weakening process of abscission.

value.value: A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) composed of a layer of cells that is part of the abscission zone (PO:0000146) that have lignin and suberin depositions and are found on the axial side of the break or exposed surface of abscission.
Parenchyma tissue containing particularly large intercellular spaces in the tissue of roots.
A portion of aerenchyma that is part of a stem.
A portion of parenchyma tissue containing particularly large intercellular spaces in the leaf mesophyll.

definition.value: If you are annotating to this term, please add an additional annotation to vascular leaf (PO:0009025) or non-vascular leaf (PO:0025075), depending on the species. All annotations for angiosperms, gymnosperms, and pteridophytes should go to vascular leaf and all annotations for bryophytes should go to non-vascular leaf.

value.value: A portion of primary phloem tissue positioned internal to the primary xylem.
A portion of seed coat epidermis (PO:0006048) which is part of the seed coat (PO:0009088) and develops from the outer surface of the inner integument (PO:0020022).
A portion of seed coat epidermis (PO:0006048) which is part of the seed coat (PO:0009088) and develops from the inner epidermis of the inner integument (PO:0020022).

A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) that is the central region of an endosperm (PO:0009089), composed of cells that are significantly larger than those at the periphery, especially the aleurone and sub-aleurone layers.

definition.value: Also called starchy endosperm region (characteristic of some grasses).

value.value: A laticifer cell (PO:0025031) that is joined longitudinally to other articulated laticifer cells to form a tube.

definition.value: The walls between contiguous cells may be perforated or may disappear completely. This terms should be used for individual cells. For multiple cells joined together, use articulated laticifer (PO:0005006).

value.value: A laticifer cell (PO:0025031) that is not joined longitudinally to other laticifer cells to form a tube.

definition.value: May be coenocytic (multi-nucleate) and branched and may grow intrusively between other plant cells (PO:0009002).

value.value: A portion of procambium (PO:0025275) tissue that undergoes differentiation to form the primary vascular tissue (PO:0025408) of a root (PO:0009005).

definition.value: A derivative of the root apical meristem.

value.value: A lateral meristem (PO:0020145) that is part of a root (PO:0009005).

definition.value: Not to be confused with lateral root apical meristem (PO:0006020), which is an apical meristem (PO:0020144) of a lateral root (PO:0020121).

value.value: A spikelet (PO:0009051) that is part of the tassel inflorescence (PO:0020126) and bears tassel florets (PO:0006310) at maturity.
A small staminate flower (PO:0025600) that is part of a tassel spikelet (PO:0006309).

definition.value: The tassel floret (PO:0006310) initiates both stamens (PO:0009029) and carpels (PO:0009030), but all carpels abort during development. Found in Zea spp.

value.value: A tassel spikelet (PO:0006309) which is the ultimate, sessile, higher order inflorescence axis (PO:0009081) of the maize tassel inflorescence (PO:0020126).

definition.value: Develops from the tassel spikelet pair meristem (PO:0006358).

value.value: A tassel spikelet (PO:0006309) which is the ultimate, pedicellate, higher order inflorescence axis (PO:0009081) of the maize tassel inflorescence (PO:0020126).

definition.value: Develops from the tassel spikelet pair meristem (PO:0006358).

label.value: lower floret of pedicellate spikelet of tassel

value.value: A tassel floret that is the lower of the two florets of a pedicellate spikelet of a tassel inflorescence.
